<subSubSection lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="495" pageId="19" pageNumber="494" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1860,2029]" box="[199,1179,1896,1921]" pageId="19" pageNumber="494">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,1017,1896,1921]" pageId="19" pageNumber="494">Recorded damage and economic importance in the orchards of Iran:</emphasis>
Not recorded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1860,2029]" pageId="19" pageNumber="494">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,946,1932,1957]" pageId="19" pageNumber="494">Recorded damage in the orchards of other parts of the world:</emphasis>
A destructive pest in the apple orchards of Syria (
<bibRefCitation box="[224,435,1968,1993]" pageId="19" pageNumber="494" refId="ref18489" refString="Dardar, M. A., Bela, H. M. R. &amp; Basheer, A. M. (2012) Observations on some biological aspects of Cicadatra persica (Cicadidae: Hemiptera) in apple fruit orchards in Erneh, Syria. Journal of Entomological and Acarological Research, 44 (12), 56 - 59. https: // doi. org / 10.4081 / jear. 2012. e 12" type="journal article">
Dardar 
<emphasis box="[311,359,1968,1993]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="494">et al</emphasis>
. 2012
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1860,2029]" box="[199,1126,2004,2029]" pageId="19" pageNumber="494">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,562,2004,2029]" pageId="19" pageNumber="494">Recorded distribution in Iran:</emphasis>
Northwest, west, southwest, centre and southeast.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,151,213]" pageId="20" pageNumber="495">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,342,151,176]" pageId="20" pageNumber="495">Conclusion:</emphasis>
In spite of the wide distribution of the species in Iran, large populations and the activity of species as pest have never been recorded.
</paragraph>
